### This file is for PyCharm HTTP Client.
### GET requests can also be opened in a browser.
### POST requests should be executed from this file (Run) or via /docs.

###

### Root (GET) - can be opened in browser:
### http://127.0.0.1:8000/
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/
Accept: application/json

###

### 1) Current weather by coordinates (GET) - can be opened in browser:
### http://127.0.0.1:8000/weather/current?lat=55.7558&lon=37.6173
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/weather/current?lat=55.7558&lon=37.6173
Accept: application/json

###

### 2) Add city and cache today's forecast (POST)
### This request cannot be opened directly in browser address bar.
### Run it from PyCharm HTTP Client or use: http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/cities
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Moscow",
  "latitude": 55.7558,
  "longitude": 37.6173
}

###

### 2) Add another city (POST)
### Run it from PyCharm HTTP Client or use: http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/cities
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Seoul",
  "latitude": 37.5665,
  "longitude": 126.9780
}

###

### 3) Get cities with available forecast (GET) - can be opened in browser:
### http://127.0.0.1:8000/cities
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/cities
Accept: application/json

###

### 4) Get weather for city at selected time (GET) - can be opened in browser:
### http://127.0.0.1:8000/cities/Moscow/weather?time=18:00
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/cities/Moscow/weather?time=18:00
Accept: application/json

###

### 4) Get weather for city at selected time with selected fields (GET) - can be opened in browser:
### http://127.0.0.1:8000/cities/Moscow/weather?time=18:00&fields=temperature,wind_speed
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/cities/Moscow/weather?time=18:00&fields=temperature,wind_speed
Accept: application/json